y_check_level":"Integration","justification":"Needs coordination between input validation (override flag) and audit-record persistence. REAL-INFRA is not explicit: behavior does not require external API contract or OS/subprocess semantics. Rejected System because text only requires an auditable record, not a real external boundary contract.","test_description":"Attempt manual override without flag and assert rejection; then with flag assert summary accepted and warning/audit record persisted and queryable via audit store module.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"After Phase 4 fixes, the gate requires a review round identifier produced after the latest fix commit before PASS can be finalized.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"This is temporal/state handoff logic across fix metadata and review-round metadata. No explicit SYSTEM TRIAD requirement in the behavior text (no external response-shape check or explicit external round-trip side-effect boundary). Rejected System because 'latest fix commit' here can be validated via integrated metadata flow without requiring real subprocess/network.","test_description":"Create fix-commit metadata and two review rounds (one before, one after fix), run gate finalization logic through integrated state services, and assert PASS allowed only when selected review round is after latest fix commit.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.22,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"In the live review loop, PASS cannot finalize unless a fresh review-agent round runs on the updated diff.","required_reality_check_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP applies: behavior explicitly depends on a real review-agent round in a live loop, and mocks can hide failures where no truly fresh agentic run occurred on updated diff. Rejected Integration because behavior is not only infrastructure around call; it requires real agent-run freshness in live flow. Rejected Workflow because this behavior specifies one required fresh agentic round, not multiple sequenced agentic decisions.","test_description":"Execute the live loop against an updated diff with real review-agent invocation enabled; assert PASS finalization is denied before new agent round and allowed only after a newly created post-update agent round id is present.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.22,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.63,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"If review rounds are exhausted with unresolved MUST-FIX findings in stored results, the outcome is escalation rather than PASS.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"Core risk is orchestration over persisted findings + round-budget state. No explicit real infra requirement and no dependence on fresh model judgment because behavior is keyed to 'stored results'. Rejected Agentic due disqualifying text 'stored results' (decision uses existing findings, not model output quality).","test_description":"Seed stored findings with unresolved MUST-FIX and set round counter to exhausted; run decision engine through service/repository path and assert escalation outcome with PASS blocked.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.11,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"In a live multi-round review workflow, exhausted rounds with unresolved MUST-FIX findings still block PASS and emit escalation.","required_reality_check_level":"Workflow","justification":"MULTI-STEP applies explicitly ('live multi-round review workflow'): correctness depends on sequenced rounds plus terminal escalation behavior. At least two agentic-stage transitions are implied across rounds, so single-step Agentic is insufficient as the minimum reality check. Rejected Integration because behavior is end-to-end multi-round orchestration in live workflow.","test_description":"Run an end-to-end live review workflow over multiple rounds on evolving diffs; ensure unresolved MUST-FIX persists until round budget exhaustion, then verify final state blocks PASS and emits escalation artifact/event.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.17,"Workflow":0.72}}]}
